	‚Ä¢	Symbiosis Operators ‚Äî collaboration and co-evolution
	‚Ä¢	Predation Operators ‚Äî pressure, selection, competitive dynamics
	‚Ä¢	Climax-State Operators ‚Äî stability, maturity, optimization
	‚Ä¢	Disturbance Operators ‚Äî fire, famine, collapse, reset

These operators allow Pantheon to think like a living system.

‚∏ª

4. CROSS-DOMAIN BRIDGES

4.1 Biology ‚Üí Engineering

Nature‚Äôs solutions (modularity, redundancy, frugality) inform design.

4.2 Ecology ‚Üí Economics

Resource cycles mirror capital flow; niches mirror markets.

4.3 Evolution ‚Üí Strategy

Selection pressure maps onto competition, innovation, and timing.

4.4 Homeostasis ‚Üí Governance

Stable systems require regulation and feedback loops.

4.5 Succession ‚Üí Innovation Cycles

Early chaos ‚Üí growth ‚Üí peak ‚Üí disruption ‚Üí rebirth.

